y. Vitruvius and Alberti expressed the meaning of architecture in their eras: Roman antiquity and the Renaissance. Hovestadt has done the same for the present day, incorporating considerations of physics, mathematics, technology, literature, and philosophy. Books I to III deal with the role of the architect and the objectivity of architecture. Books IV to VI address the modalities of speaking about and encoding architecture: the secret, the public, and the private. Books VII to X are dedicated to actual digital mechanisms: artificial intelligence, natural communication, gnomonics, and cultural heritage. An architectural treatise for our age in 10 books Inspired by the works of Vitruvius and Alberti Published in three volumes in the Applied Virtuality Book Series Ludger Hovestadt, professor of architecture and CAAD, ETH Zurich  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aAlberti. 4aAntike. 4aArchitektur. 4aArchitekturtheorie. 4aComputerwissenschaft. 4aDesign. 4aDigitale Architektur. 4aEnergie. 4aHumanismus. 4aKommunikation. 4aMaterial. 4aMathematik. 4aMedien. 4aNatur. 4aRationalismus. 4aRenaissance. 4aVitruvius. 7aARCHITECTURE / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aCommunication, Design, Energy, Humanism, Material, Media, Nature, Rationalism, Renaissance, Architecture theory, Computer Science.1 aBühlmann, Vera, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHovestadt, Ludger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2022z9783110992793oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz97831109928160